    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> But now the test is less specific, I mean the test could pass while the usage would not be up to date or completely broken.\n\nThat was actually the case :). The usage message was out of sync with the jsdoc that itself was out of sync with the code. Even before my feature. Still, we had a green test.\n\nWith the regexp the test is less specific (we only test that we fire a usage warning in case of bad usage, without checking the usage message), but at least this will not give us a false sense of security.\n\nI don't think testing for a full string equality here will help us, this is just a copy-paste magnet and in the end the correctness of the usage message is not tested, we just test that this is the same string in the code and the tests.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-20T23:02:43Z",
